SAMARA, Russia – Uruguay beat 10-man Russia 3-0 on Monday to top World Cup Group A with three wins out of three as the host nation qualified for the next round in second place. READ: Uruguay, Russia qualify for World Cup last 16, Egypt, Saudi Arabia out Luis Suarez opened the scoring in the 10th minute and the South Americans extended their lead with the help of a Denis Cheryshev own goal midway through the first half. Edinson Cavani added a late third. Uruguay and Russia lock down their spots in the Round of 16 ---------- pic.twitter.com/iZENDPvr1h AFP